    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-12-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="242"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <head>No. 242.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Marsh</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Borne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-12-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 27, 1871</date>. (Received January
                        18.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 392.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your instruction No. 326 relating to services rendered the United States ship
                    Guerriere by officers of the Italian navy, and to inclose a copy of a note
                    which, in fulfillment of that instruction, I have addressed to the minister of
                    foreign affairs.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEORGE P. MARSH.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Marsh</persName> to Visconti
                                <persName type="to">Venosta</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States.</hi>, <hi
                                    rend="italic">Borne</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-12-27">
                                <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 27, 1871</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi> As the best method of complying with the
                        orders of my Government in relation to services rendered to the United
                        States ship of war Guerriere by officers of the Italian navy, I have the
                        honor to inclose you copies of a recent instruction on that subject from the
                        Secretary of State of the United States, and of a communication from the
                        Secretary of the Navy to the State Department.</p>
                    <p>I avail myself of the occasion to renew to you the assurance of my high
                        consideration.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>GEORGE P. MARSH.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>The Noble Chevalier <hi rend="smallcaps">Visconti Venosta</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister of Foreign Affairs.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
